\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #1
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset

The spot price of cocoa today is 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{0}=\$2,500$
\end_inset

 per metric ton.
 The one-year forward price for cocoa is 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{0,1}=\$2,750$
\end_inset

.
 A buyer and seller agree to enter a forward contract for one ton of cocoa.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
1.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 If the spot price in one year is 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}=\$2,600$
\end_inset

, what is the payoff to the long party? The short party? How much money
 is exchanged at origination?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
2.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Plot the payoff to the long forward as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 What is the minimum and maximum payoff?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
3.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Plot the payoff to the short forward as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 What is the minimum and maximum payoff?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #1 solutions
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #1 solutions
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
1.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The payoff to the long party is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}X_{1} & =S_{1}-F_{0,1}\\
 & =2,600-2,750\\
 & =-150
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

 The payoff to the short party is:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}-X_{1} & =F_{0,1}-S_{1}\\
 & =150
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

 No money is exchanged hands on the origination date.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #1 solutions
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #1 solutions
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Itemize
The minimum payoff to the long party is 
\begin_inset Formula $0-F_{0,1}=-2,750.$
\end_inset

 If 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{1}$
\end_inset

 is unbounded above, the maximum payoff is 
\begin_inset Formula $+\infty$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


