\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset

 A farmer is planning to grow 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

 metric ton of cocoa.
 The farmer plans to sell the crop precisely one year from today.
 The cost of producing cocoa is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$2,300$
\end_inset

 per metric ton.
 Answer the following:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
1.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Is the farmer long or short cocoa? Graph the farmer's profit as a function
 of cocoa prices in one year.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
2.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 How can the farmer hedge her exposure using forwards?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
3.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The one-year forward price is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$2,600$
\end_inset

.
 Graph the payoff of the forward as a function of cocoa prices in one year.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
4.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Suppose the farmer hedges using forwards.
 What is her profit if the spot price in one year is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$2,000$
\end_inset

? 
\begin_inset Formula $\$2,600?$
\end_inset


\end_layout

