\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Technical note on interest rates
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Throughout the semester, we will assume there is a single risk-free interest
 rate of 
\begin_inset Formula $r\geq0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Risk-free cash flows should be discounted at the risk-free rate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{T}\geq0$
\end_inset

 is a risk-free cash flow at time 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

, then the price of this cash flow at date 
\begin_inset Formula $t<T$
\end_inset

 is given by:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
B_{t}=\begin{cases}
\frac{B_{T}}{(1+r)^{T-t}} & \text{if }r\text{ is discretely compounded}\\
\\
B_{T}e^{-r(T-t)} & \text{if }r\text{ is continuously compounded}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator parbreak
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Practice problem #3
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
1.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Suppose the discretely compounded risk-free rate is 
\begin_inset Formula $r=0.05$
\end_inset

 and today is date 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

.
 What is the price of a risk-free bond that pays 
\begin_inset Formula $\$100$
\end_inset

 at date 
\begin_inset Formula $T=1$
\end_inset

?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
2.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Suppose today is date 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0$
\end_inset

.
 The price of a risk-free bond that pays 
\begin_inset Formula $\$110$
\end_inset

 at date 
\begin_inset Formula $T=1$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\$100$
\end_inset

.
 What is the discretely compounded risk-free rate?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

